hip vs the index/sector, and tradeability.","why_it_can_fail":"corporate-action gaps, illiquid names, or a short listing history can distort returns/DMA/RS."}},"business":{"ok":true,"is_bank":false,"flags":[{"label":"Business quality","value":65.8,"unit":"/100","status":"ok","read":"Average quality (66/100).","meaning":"Composite of profitability, return on capital, balance-sheet safety and cash conversion (the Fundamentals-tab Quality score).","why_useful":"A durable, high-return business compounds value; a low-quality one needs a bigger margin of safety.","why_it_can_fail":"A single composite can mask a weak component; open the Fundamentals tab for the breakdown."},{"label":"Cash conversion","value":0.41,"unit":"\u00d7","status":"weak","read":"Only 0.41\u00d7 \u2014 profit not turning into cash (watch receivables/inventory).","meaning":"Median of (cash from operations \u00f7 net profit) over the last 5 years.","why_useful":"Profit you can't collect as cash is fragile; >0.8\u00d7 means earnings are real cash, <0.6\u00d7 is an accrual red flag.","why_it_can_fail":"One-off working-capital swings or a capex year can distort a single ratio; the 5-yr median smooths it."},{"label":"Balance-sheet safety","value":0.23,"unit":"\u00d7 D/E","status":"good","read":"Conservatively financed (D/E 0.23\u00d7, interest cover 5.4\u00d7).","meaning":"Latest debt-to-equity and interest coverage (EBIT \u00f7 interest) from the balance sheet.","why_useful":"Low debt and high interest cover let a business survive a downturn; high debt amplifies trouble.","why_it_can_fail":"Off-balance-sheet leases/guarantees aren't captured; a cash-rich firm can show low D/E yet still be risky elsewhere."},{"label":"Earnings momentum","value":65.06,"unit":"% YoY","status":"good","read":"Profit up 65% YoY (latest TTM) and accelerating.","meaning":"Trailing-twelve-month net profit vs the year-ago TTM (and whether the YoY rate is rising = 'accelerating').","why_useful":"Improving, accelerating earnings tend to drive re-rating; falling profit warns of a deteriorating business.","why_it_can_fail":"TTM can be lumpy for cyclicals/one-offs; cross-check the multi-year trend on the Fundamentals tab."}]},"valuation":{"ok":true,"is_bank":false,"pe_now":13.0,"pe_percentile":34.0,"median_pe":15.3,"earnings_yield_pct":7.69,"pb":1.32,"ev_ebitda":8.98,"quality_score":66.0,"pat_cagr_5y_pct":6.5,"peg":2.0,"cheapness":{"status":"ok","read":"P/E at the 34-percentile of its 10-yr range \u2014 mid-range vs its own history."},"expectations":"At 13.0\u00d7 earnings for ~6% 5-yr profit CAGR, the market is paying \u22482.00\u00d7 growth (PEG). >2 = a lot already priced in; <1 = cheap if growth holds. This PEG divides TTM P/E by TRAILING 5-year annual PAT CAGR (endpoint-to-endpoint) \u2014 a time-axis mismatch vs the textbook FORWARD-EPS PEG, and one abnormal base/terminal year distorts the CAGR. A rough trailing valuation-vs-growth gauge, not a precise forward PEG.","cyclical_caveat":null,"meaning":"P/E percentile = where today's price-to-earnings sits within the stock's own last-10-yr range (low = cheap vs its past). Paired with the Quality score and 5-yr profit growth so a cheap multiple is judged against business strength, not in isolation.","why_useful":"Cheapness only matters relative to quality and growth \u2014 a low P/E on a declining or peak-cyclical business is a trap, not a bargain.","why_it_can_fail":"P/E breaks for loss-makers / one-offs; for banks use P/B not EV/EBITDA; a multiple cheap vs history can stay cheap if the business has structurally de-rated."},"ownership":{"ok":true,"na":null,"holders":{"Promoter":{"periods":["Sep 2023","Dec 2023","Mar 2024","Jun 2024","Sep 2024","Dec 2024","Mar 2025","Jun 2025","Sep 2025","Dec 2025","Mar 2026"],"values":[64.63,64.63,64.63,64.63,64.63,64.63,65.01,65.01,65.01,66.18,66.47],"latest_pct":66.47,"chg_1y_pp":1.46},"FII":{"periods":["Sep 2023","Dec 2023","Mar 2024","Jun 2024","Sep 2024","Dec 2024","Mar 2025","Jun 2025","Sep 2025","Dec 2025","Mar 2026"],"values":[3.87,2.53,0.53,0.18,0.02,0.62,0.18,0.24,0.17,0.34,0.14],"latest_pct":0.14,"chg_1y_pp":-0.04},"DII":{"periods":["Sep 2023","Dec 2023","Mar 2024","Jun 2024","Sep 2024","Dec 2024","Mar 2025","Jun 2025","Sep 2025","Dec 2025","Mar 2026"],"values":[10.72,6.61,3.47,2.65,1.84,1.7,1.79,1.97,2.05,0.43,0.09],"latest_pct":0.09,"chg_1y_pp":-1.7},"Public":{"periods":["Sep 2023","Dec 2023","Mar 2024","Jun 2024","Sep 2024","Dec 2024","Mar 2025","Jun 2025","Sep 2025","Dec 2025","Mar 2026"],"values":[20.79,26.24,31.37,32.56,33.52,33.05,33.03,32.8,32.77,33.05,33.3],"latest_pct":33.3,"chg_1y_pp":0.27}},"pledge":null,"events":[{"date":"23-Aug-2024","subject":"Dividend - Re 0.50 Per Share","materiality":"Low"},{"date":"28-Aug-2024","subject":"Annual General Meeting","materiality":"Med"},{"date":"01-Aug-2025","subject":"Dividend - Re 0.50 Per Share","materiality":"Low"},{"date":"30-Jan-2026","subject":"Interim Dividend - Re 0.75 Per Share","materiality":"Low"}],"placeholders":[{"label":"Promoter pledge (detail)","note":"share-level pledge history \u2014 fetchable via NSE, deferred to MVP-2."},{"label":"Bulk / block deals","note":"large on-market trades \u2014 NSE feed, deferred to MVP-2."},{"label":"Insider / SAST disclosures","note":"promoter & designated-person dealings \u2014 deferred to MVP-2."},{"label":"Exchange announcements","note":"NSE/BSE filings stream \u2014 deferred to MVP-2."},{"label":"Results calendar","note":"next board-meeting / results date \u2014 deferred to MVP-2."},{"label":"Credit ratings","note":"rating-agency actions \u2014 deferred to MVP-2."}],"reads":{"Promoter":"Promoter stake up 1.46pp over ~1yr \u2192 66.47%.","FII":"FIIs reducing (-0.04pp YoY \u2192 0.14%).","DII":"DIIs reducing (-1.70pp YoY \u2192 0.09%)."},"meaning":"Quarterly shareholding (% held by Promoters / Foreign (FII) / Domestic (DII) institutions / Public) from Screener, plus exchange corporate actions tagged by materiality (High = structural: bonus/split/buyback/merger; L